    "answer_id" : 10723570,
    "question_id" : 6167266,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>I´d say <a href=\"http://www.eclipse.org/MoDisco/\" rel=\"nofollow\">MoDisco</a> is by far the most powerful one (though probably not the easiest one to work with).</p>\n\n<p>MoDisco is a generic reverse engineering framework (so that you can customize your reverse engineering project, with MoDisco you can even reverse engineer the behaviour of the java methods, not only the structure and signatures) but also includes some predefined features like the generation of class diagrams out of Java code that you need.</p>\n"
